claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: A flow chart depicting subject participation in the study, showing numbers allocated to different treatment groups and safety populations (e.g., Safety Population n=2344 and n=2304). does not support the claim: the figure only shows a flow chart of participant enrollment and safety populations, with no information on hemagglutinin content per strain in Flublok or standard-dose influenza vaccines.
